verbose_text: Aside from Vigna radiata, particularly high levels of E-2-HAL were found in the members of the cucurbitacea family including Momordica charantia (43,236 +/- 14,777 ng/g FW), Bryonia dioica (38,696 +/- 7502 ng/g FW), and Cucumis sativa (14,524 +/- 1137 ng/g FW), as well as in Ruellia simplex (49,369 +/- 5967 ng/g FW).
